# UpForge AI model north star

UpForge will train a **proprietary gameplay model** (Valorant → CS2) once funded. Treat product decisions as **revenue + consented structured data**, not storage alone.

Full strategy: `docs/AI-MODEL-STRATEGY.md` · Upload/analyse model: `docs/UPLOAD-VS-ANALYSIS.md`

## Upload ≠ analyse

Cloud save and AI coaching are **separate user actions** with **separate quotas**. Never bundle them in copy or defaults unless the user explicitly chooses both.

## When planning features, prefer work that:

1. **Retains structured VODs** — archive-only cloud save (no analysis quota burn), tiered retention, clip cloud sync
2. **Captures labels** — analysis feedback, coach review, clip ↔ `analysisJobId` ↔ round linkage
3. **Preserves metadata** — match ID, agent, map, rank, timeline JSON on every cloud object
4. **Separates consent** — playback/storage opt-in ≠ training opt-in; never assume uploads are trainable

## High-leverage backlog (both revenue and corpus)

- Cloud archive API · Pro retention · training opt-in toggle · insight feedback UI · PPA at quota/disk choke points

## Avoid

- Features that only move MP4s without metadata or consent
- Training on data without explicit user consent
- Short retention that deletes future eval/training sets without user upgrade path

## Evaluate proposals with

> Does this increase MRR **or** grow consented, structured gameplay signal?

Prefer both.
